<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-067-140 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 260 821</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Design  Sept 1991 v30 n12 p38(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New multimedia chip sets aimed at niche applications.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wilson, Dave.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Multimedia systems must be capable of acquiring, processing,storing, and retrieving audio and video data.andP;  The currentindustry standards are so varied that there is not one chip setthat can satisfy all the different criteria.andP;  Although the JPEG(Joint Photographic Experts Group) and the MPEG (Motion PictureExperts Group) have come up with multimediacompression/decompression multimedia standards they are by nomeans mandatory for new products.andP;  Consequently, non-compatibleofferings may prove to be a more cost-effective answer tomultimedia questions.andP;  Philips/Signetics new SAA7199 digital videoencoder accepts seven different digital formats and allowscomputer designers to create products that let users outputdigital video to videotape recorders for storage or to televisionmonitors.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Multimedia TechnologyAnalysisStandardizationData CompressionConnectivityImage ProcessingProduct IntroductionEncodersDigital Communications.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotographchart.andO;Caption:   Desktop video with video encoder. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>